pip install -- installed the specified software, in this case Django
pip list - lists the assets in the virtual environment.
deactivate -- deactivates the virtual environment 
pip3 list is shorter since it doesn't have Django in its scope
source myEnvironments/py3Env/bin/activate - activates the virtual environment again
pip install Django==1.11.9 -- doesn't install since it already has
pip freeze  -- used for outputting in requirements format
pip freeze > requirements.txt -- the required assets, including Django, with version
pip uninstall Django -- uninstalls 
pip show Django -- shows the environment
pip search Flask -- finds all the Flask files
